post_text: POCS will open for students in a virtual/remote environment for students starting September 8, 2020 - We will phase in our instructional model, and all students will start the 2020-21 school year in a virtual/remote learning environment for the first six weeks. Our Board of Directors has modified the first day of school to be Tuesday, September 8, which allows our administrators, staff, and educators additional time to prepare for an improved virtual/remote start. Further details about our reopening plan will be finalized in the next week. http://edne.tw/n654441

post_text:
Ms. Shante' O'kelley has been a member of the POCS' family for half of this school year. She will be graduating from Delaware State University this coming December!

Ms. O'kelley was active in the Navy for 6 years and is now in the Reserves. She knew from a very young age that she loved helping kids and wanted to pursue her passion of putting smiles on their faces. Ms. O'kelley is married and has a very cute 7 year old daughter.

Kudos to Ms. O'kelley on her upcoming graduation; the POCS family is happy to have her! 🙌🎉

#pocsrocks #pocsproud #pocsstrong

Mr. Chris Steele has been a member of the POCS' family for 10 years. After graduating college with the plan to be a graphic designer, he landed a job working with kids. It was during this time that he realized that he liked helping people and how self-rewarding a career with his community's youth really was.

Thank goodness he found POCS, or should we say that POCS found him 🙌🎉🥳

post_text:
Modified Spring Break - As we come to the close of our second week of remote learning, we approach what would have been our Spring Break. Unfortunately, as many of you know, we are working in unprecedented time. With the closure of schools, we have been required to modify our school calendar in order to meet the required number of hours for our students.

As a result of this, our school will be closed for a modified Spring Break on Friday, April 10 and Monday, April 13 – there will be no Zoom sessions or classes held on those two days. Our classes and Zoom sessions will resume on Tuesday, April 14. http://edne.tw/n629079

post_text: To all of our families that are in need of meal options during our school closure, please check this information to find a location.
shared_text:
Delaware Department of Education (DDOE)
March 17 at 10:15 PM ·

Delaware schools are currently offering free student meals at 117 locations. Families can visit any of the sites - the site does not need to be in your home district or at the school your student attends.

We are continually updating de.gov/covid19edu with new meal site locations. The last update was at 3:30pm today.

Governor John Carney
Delaware Department of Health and Social Services (DHSS)

Positive Outcomes Charter School Closed - March 16 to March 27 - In accordance with Governor Carney’s decision, and in order to help prevent the spread of the coronavirus, the Positive Outcomes Charter School will be closed beginning on Monday, March 16, 2020, until March 27, 2020.
We will continue to keep POCS families informed through various communication tools, including our website, social media, and email.

We ask that 12-month employees check school email for communications regarding work schedules during this time period.
http://edne.tw/n619864

post_text:
We still have a number of tags left on the tree! If you want to help out our families in need this Holiday season, please come in, grab a tag, and return by December 18th! If you’re unable to grab a tag, you can also donate money through a link on POCS’ website and that money will go toward purchasing the left over gifts off the tree!

————————————

POCS Holiday Giving Tree - Positive Outcomes Charter School has chosen to adopt multiple students in need this holiday season. Our Giving Tree is decorated in the lobby with tags that contain items for our students in need after Thanksgiving break. If you would like to donate a gift to one of our students, please take a tag and return your gift, with the tag, by Wednesday, December 18, 2019. You can also make a donation through our school website to help with purchasing any items left on the Giving Tree. In previous years, this event has been a huge success thanks to the help of our parents, students and staff. Thank you all in advance for helping these students this holiday season. http://edne.tw/n601287

PROJECT SEARCH LOOKING FOR POTENTIAL APPLICANTS

post_text:
Do you know a child who is frustrated with school?
Do you know a child who has a learning disability that is hurting his/her achievement?
Do you know a child who has a difficult time dealing with large classes?
Do you know a child who has given up on school?
Do you know a child who completes work and then lose it?
Do you know a child who has ADD/ADHD that is hurting his/her achievement?
Do you know a child who is returning from mental health treatment, and is struggling upon return to a large school?
If you answered yes to any of the above questions, we may be the right school for that student.
Positive Outcomes Charter School
Serving 7th through 12th Students.

post_text: Good news deserves to be shared again!
shared_text:
Delaware Charter Schools Network
December 21, 2018 at 3:42 PM ·

Good Morning Charter Community!!! Having a Positive Outcomes Charter School, Freire Charter School Wilmington, Great Oaks Charter School Wilmington, Newark Charter School, Kuumba Academy Charter School, First State Military Academy, Delaware Design-Lab High School(Design Thinking Academy) kind of morning today.

What an awesome way to head into holiday break!! All SEVEN charter schools had their charters renewed by the Delaware Department of Education (DDOE) with the assent of the DE State Board of Education! An amazing amount of work goes into renewal - great work done by all of our teams!

While 6 of the 7 schools received five-year charters, Newark Charter received a 10-year charter!! Only the second school in DE to do so. Woohoo!!

Dover AFB EFMP Family Support
August 28, 2018 at 1:21 AM ·

PLEASE READ: When you receive this form in the stack of paperwork you need to fill out and return to school, PLEASE do not ignore it. Every public school in Delaware will send this home. The purpose is to ensure that educators and support personnel (SLO included!) know where to direct resources and supports for military connected students. It is NOT tied to tracking performance or accountability as a demographic sub-group. It is available in English and Spanish, and if you have questions feel free to contact me at sonya.dyer.1@us.af.mil. Thank you...and please help spread the word!

post_text: Positive Outcomes Charter School Receives Recognition School Award - Positive Outcomes Charter School was recognized by the Delaware Department of Education as a Recognition School Award Recipient. The awards are given (a) to schools whose students are performing at an exceptionally high level, particularly those schools with large percentages of students coming from low-income households and (b) to schools that have succeeded in closing the achievement gap for students such as low-income students, students from minority groups and students with disabilities. http://edne.tw/n492950

POCS Now Closed 1/4/18 (Change In Status) - After reviewing weather conditions in many of the areas in which our students and staff reside this late evening/early morning, Positive Outcomes Charter School will now be closed today, January 4, 2018. Our school has students enrolled from 10 different school districts across our State. The safety of our Students and Staff is our number one priority.

In the event that the CR school district chooses to open, do not send POCS students on the busses. There will be no one at the school to receive them.

12-month employees should not report to work.

Thank you and if you do have to travel today, please be safe.
http://edne.tw/n487905

post_text: POCS Holiday Adopt a Family - The Holiday season is upon us! Once again, Positive Outcomes Charter School has set up our holiday gift giving tree in our front lobby. The purpose of this tree is to help students in need throughout the holiday season. We are asking our POCS community and family to help support each other by donating a gift. If you and/or your family are interested in supporting this cause, please choose a tag from our holiday tree or make a donation towards a gift for a student. When selecting a tag, we ask that you please wrap the gift and attach the tag you chose so staff members can make sure that your gift is given to the correct family. All gifts and/or donations should be returned to the school no later than Monday, December 18th. Gifts will be distributed to families at the conclusion of our Holiday luncheon on Thursday, December 21st. In previous years, we have been fortunate to help many students and families in need during the holidays and we couldn’t do that without your support. Thank you for your continued support! http://edne.tw/n483643
